HEADWORD: Squamata
<hw>Squa*ma"ta</hw> <pr>(skw⟦adot⟧*m⟦amac⟧"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>squamatus</ets> scaly.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of edentates having the body covered
with large, imbricated horny scales. It includes the
pangolins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

